name: Cranberry Liqueur
description:
The perfect mix of sweet, sour and tart.

Made from Great Lakes cranberries and a mix of natural botanicals that enhance the berries, Tattersall Cranberry is a unique companion to your favorite spirits. Add a splash to your cosmopolitan, mix with a hard cider or top off your gin and tonic.

Sweet, sour and tart, balanced by an herbal finish.

name: Crème De Fleur Floral Liqueur
description:
A balancing act of six aromatic flowers.

Tattersall Crème de Fleur is distilled with six flowers and
post-macerated with additional flowers for a beautifully concentrated flavor and aroma.

Floral, sweet and perfectly balanced.

name: Crème de Cacao Chocolate Liqueur
description: Rich, bold chocolate flavors complement smooth vanilla notes.

name: Easy Street Natural Flavored Whiskey
description: Tattersall Distilling Company from United States, provided by Tattersall LLC. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Fernet Liqueur
description:
Cleanses and awakens your senses like no other.

The product of more than 30 botanicals, spices and herbs,
Tattersall Fernet is an intensely complex liqueur that will pique your curiosity.

Unlike any other liqueur, its flavor and sensation engages every corner of your palate.

name: Freewheeler Pommeau
description:
A unique collaboration with Sociable Cider Werks.

This pommeau is made from brandy distilled from Sociable Cider Werks Freewheeler Dry Apple and combined with its unfermented cider base and then rested on oak. Try it chilled and neat or to add a real apple flavor to your favorite cocktails.

Bright, slightly sweet and tart, true to the cider apples.

name: Gin
description:
A New World gin born from Old World wisdom.

Crafted with 22 carefully selected botanicals from around the globe, Tattersall Gin is our flagship for a reason — smooth and textured with just the right bite.

Distilled from 100% Certified Organic Corn Neutral Grain Spirits.

Citrus aromas complement a captivating balance of juniper, earth, and spice.

name: Grapefruit Crema Liqueur
description:
Bold, fresh and beautiful.

Made with a careful balance of flowers and grapefruit zest,
Tattersall Grapefruit Crema bursts with flavor unlike any other. Use in place of triple sec or Curaçao for a delicious twist.

Grapefruit Crema Liqueur.

name: Italiano Liqueur
description:
Warm, spicy and just the right amount of bitterness.

Tattersall Italiano Style is a wine-based liqueur made from fermented and distilled grapes, infused with a distinct blend of botanicals. You can sip it on the rocks, in a Manhattan or any drink that calls for sweet vermouth.

Sweet and herbal with notes of orange, vanilla and cocoa.

name: Key Lime Flavored Gin + Tonic
description: Tattersall Distilling Company from United States, provided by Tattersall LLC. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Lime Crema Liqueur
description:
Beyond a splash of lime. 

Made from a distinct blend of lime, citrus and botanicals, Tattersall Lime Crema is a lively addition to your liqueur lineup. Add a robust citrus kick to the classics or simply mix with soda water.

Intense lime notes balance a refreshing aroma and subtle spice backbone.

name: Manhattan
description: Our 100% rye whiskey lends a peppery backbone with notes of toffee and maple. Whiskey is aged no less than two years and mellowed with a dash of our herbal Italiano Liqueur (reminiscent of sweet vermouth), sherry (which lends a nutty flavor), and aromatic bitters. Baking spice on the nose and perfectly balanced and round on the palate with minimal sweetness.

description: Our 100% rye whiskey lends a peppery backbone with notes of toffee and maple. description: Those vessels have had a profound influence on the final spirit, noticeable from the get-go via its vibrant red reflections. The aromas and flavors land with punchy gusto, delivering a complex and nuanced experience. Pronounced earthy and vegetal notes mean it will win over just as many Scotch drinkers as those who normally opt for rye or bourbon.

name: Premium Blend Rested On Oak Spiced Rum
description: Tattersall Distilling Company from United States, provided by Tattersall LLC. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

Tattersall Sour Cherry is the crafted with Montmorency cherries and aged in American oak barrels to create the perfect marriage of sweet and sour.

Intense taste of Montmorency cherries complemented by American oak.

name: Straight Rye Whiskey
description:
Big, bold and spicy.

Tattersall Straight Rye Whiskey is a Monongahela-style whiskey distilled from 100% Minnesota rye, grown and harvested 50 miles north of the distillery in Cambridge, MN. Perfect for rye purists, it’s aged for at least two years in 30 and 53 gallon charred white oak, sourced and coopered in Minnesota. Think of it as Bourbon’s bolder cousin. Enjoy it neat or in classics like an Old Fashioned or Manhattan.

Aromas of vanilla, maple, and mellow oak. Robust and peppery on the palate with lingering notes of caramel.

name: Tightline Mildwestern Organic Vodka
description: Clean, crisp and powered by the sun. Distilled from 100% Midwestern corn, Tightline Organic Vodka is made to reflect the spirit of the great outdoors. Quite possibly the smoothest, most neutral organic vodka out there, it’s the perfect base for all your favorite vodka cocktails.

name: Friuli Aquileia Pinot Grigio
description:

Bouquet: Fresh and youthful, with hints of acacia flowers and subtle spicy tones. 
Flavour: Appealingly full-flavored; very well-balanced and persistent.

name: Friuli Aquileia Sauvignon
description: It is a Sauvignon Blanc that, on the nose, reveals hints of Mediterranean broom and tropical fruits, made even more elegant by the floral caress of hawthorn. It has the finesse of a Loire wine combined with the warmth of the Mediterranean. Its aromatic style makes it ideal for bringing out the best in fish, seafood and vegetable-based dishes, but it is also an excellent accompaniment for ethnic cuisines. It is a “glocal” wine: one that contains the roots and spirit of Friuli - from which it comes - as well as an international flavour.

name: Friuli Aquileia Sauvignon Aquilis
description: This wine is a mosaic as fascinating as those of Aquileia, the zone of origin of this white which contains the colours of gold and of emerald, the freshness of Alpine breezes and the tang of the sea. It is a Sauvignon Blanc that, on the nose, reveals hints of Mediterranean broom and tropical fruits, made even more elegant by the floral caress of hawthorn. It has the fi nesse of a Loire wine combined with the warmth of the Mediterranean.

name: Prosecco Brut
description: Our Prosecco is attractive pale straw-yellow color with a lively, persistent perlage and a rich mousse. The bouquet is refined and elegant with beautiful mineral notes, elegant white flowers and stone fruits, enhanced by pleasing fruity notes. The palate is dry and pleasantly fruity with a fresh, aromatic note on the finish.

name: Veneto Polvaro Oro Bianco
description: Four outstanding grape varieties provide the framework for this distinctive white blend. Chardonnay, Pinot Grigio, Verduzzo, and Traminer are combined to offer refreshing fruit flavors of honeydew, apricot, and pink grapefruit. Added scents of honeysuckle and white pepper result in a soft, dry wine that is excellent for either food pairing or simply sipping.

name: Venezia Cabernet Sauvignon
description: The intense ruby ​​color of the Tenuta Polvaro Cabernet Sauvignon D.O.C. is completed with aromas of red fruits, in particular blackberry, blueberry, as well as hints of black pepper and tobacco leaves. Complex and taut in the mouth, it’s the ideal pairing for red meats, cheeses and chocolate.

name: Venezia Polvaro Nero
description: Merlot, Cabernet Sauvignon and Malbech infuse the Tenuta Polvaro Nero D.O.C. a great personality with a soft and velvety texture and a unique aromatic note, which ranges between hints of plum, black cherry, blackberry, cocoa, tobacco and coffee. On the palate, it is full and enveloping, ideal when paired with grilled meats, roasts and hard cheeses.

name: 22 Islay Dry Gin
description:
The Botanist is a gin of layered complexity.
A progressive exploration of the botanical heritage of our isle of islay. 22 hand-foraged local botanicals delicately augment nine berries, barks, seeds and peels during an achingly slow distillation. This first and only Islay dry gin is a rare expression of the heart and soul of our remote Scottish island.

name: Limited Release 10 Years Old Copper Alley Oloroso Sherry Cask Finish Single Malt Irish Whiskey
description:
Enticing on the nose, the liquid is abounding with sweet aromas of delicate honey, floral notes of apple blossom and some dried red fruits.

The casks were aging Oloroso sherry for over 30 years, which is evidenced by the rich palate of deep fruit notes of baked plums, ripe red grapes and serves to give the liquid its deep amber hue. This luscious drop has a long lingering finish of rich, dark chocolate.

name: Limited Release Batch #02 13 Years Old Murder Lane Tokaj Cask Finish Single Malt Irish Whiskey
description: This delectable tipple has notes of sweet coconut, toffee and a juicy hint of honey dew melon. Surprisingly delicate on the palate initially with vanilla sweetness, ripe pears and apricot jam. A drop of water uncovers the darker notes beneath, with more wood influence, a rich earthiness and some darker chocolate notes. Finish is medium to long, with biscuit flavours and a warming pineapple rind.

name: Limited Release Batch #02 16 Year Old Keeper's Coin Pedro Ximénez Cask Finish Single Malt Whiskey
description: This decadent dram tempts the nose with soft cinnamon, vanilla essence and gooseberry. The palate swarms with rich notes of blackcurrant, smoky tobacco, coconut and dark chocolate. Medium to long finish with lingering wood spice, bitter dark chocolate, and desiccated coconut.

name: The Black Axe Smoky & Rich Blended Malt Scotch Whiskey
description: Every batch of Gladstone Axe Black Axe is made from 100% malted barley and aged in oak barrels. The Black Axe is made from a selection of malt whiskies from 14 different Highland and Islay malt Distilleries. What separates the Black Axe from American Oak is a higher percentage of Islay whisky which is smokier and spicier in its nature. The marriage of these different whiskies makes for a delicious flavor profile that can be enjoyed by scotch lovers both new and old.

name: Grenache En passerillage Santa Maria Valley
description: Medium healthy red color, with nary a sign of brown at the rim. Nose of strawberry/rhubarb and peach, with a possible suggestion of citrus, viz. blood orange. Definite notes of autumnal spice - cloves, allspice and hints of sandalwood or other scented candle one might find in the boudoir of an ageing hippie. Good volume on the palate: the wine seems to expand with exposure to air in the way that inspirational Pinot/Burgundy sometimes does. Not at all densely tannic, but extremely persistent on the palate. Contradicting all the received wisdom: Grenache is a grape capable of great elegance and complexity (as this wine shows) and one certainly destined to live for many years.

Similar elements emerge on the sip, with açai and black pepper proving most prominent as the wine spreads its wings.

Body : Bergamot orange, mouth-coating nougat, a slight minerality, tied together with a hint of coconut, banana and a brief pear note.
Finish : Sweet, lingering finish with a dry wood prickle flavors from the Oloroso Sherry cask.

name: P.X I Love You Single Malt Irish Whiskey
description:
Nose : Fantastically delicious sherry nose. Dried berries, raisins, cherries and sultanas/ golden raisins, with candied orange and sticky brown/ demerara sugar.

Palate : Wood forward opening, with an incredibly viscous yet crisp palate. The dried fruits and brown sugar from the nose are joined on the palate by walnut, zesty citrus and a hint of leather.

Finish : Walnut, dried fruits and the subtle wood prickle remain for a lengthy dry finish with a subtle hint of dark chocolate.

Palate : The palate is rewarded with a unique combination of attractive flavors - a balance of stewed apples, pears and malt with a gentle hint of nuttiness.

It has the friendliness of bourbon and the structure of Scotch with notes of butterscotch, fresh pineapple, lemon zest, and white pepper.

name: Lake superior Vodka
description: Lake Superior contains 10% of the world's fresh water. Lake Superior Vodka is distilled and cut from this astonishingly pure water plus a base of malted barley. Our vodka is deep, smooth, and clear, a fitting tribute to the Greatest of Lakes and the city at its Zenith. The warmth and shy sweetness of barley and the strong clean heart of Lake Superior water. A hint of honey and vanilla on the nose, the flavor is crisp, smooth, and memorable.

name: Lake superior Vodka

name: Maple Cask Finished Port Barrel Aged Sugarbush Whiskey
description: Our first whiskey, and, as far as we can tell, the first whiskey ever to be produced in Duluth (legally, hehe)! We age a bourbon mash in used port barrels with soft maple staves, then we finish it in bourbon casks that have been used for aging maple syrup.  Light but complex in flavor with notes of maple, roasted cherry, leather, and yellow cake.

name: Ovrevann Aquavit Liqueur
description: The Ojibwe call it “Gichi-gami,” meaning “big water.” French explorers called it “Le Lac Superieur,” meaning “Upper Lake.” Following the French and Indian War, the English kept the name, “on account of its being superior in magnitude.” Lake Superior is, in fact, the world’s largest body of freshwater. Our unaged (aka taffel-style) aquavit is named Ovrevann, Norwegian for Upper Lake, or Lake Superior. Light and aromatic, it is piquant and refreshing to sip alongside smoked.

name: Sauvignon Blanc Marlborough
description: Whitehaven captures intense notes of passionfruit, lemongrass and white peach in this crisp, refreshing Sauvignon Blanc. Superbly structured and elegantly balanced, with fresh-snipped greens and citrus characteristics that blend effortlessly with notes of tropical fruit. Each glass boasts the long, clean finish of classic Marlborough Sauvignon Blanc. With its bright character and crisp finish, Whitehaven Sauvignon Blanc pairs beautifully with a wide range of dishes. A chilled glass of Whitehaven is particularly refreshing alongside fresh seafood, spicy Asian dishes, grilled chicken or summer salads with fruits and veggies picked straight from the garden.

name: Comte Lafond Sancerre
description:
Beautiful crystalline dress, pale gold. 

The olfactory expression opens immediately on a succession of shades that are constantly renewed. First citrus fruits (orange peel and lemon), then summer fruits (white peach and pear) finally honey notes on a subtle background of peppermint... an excellent complexity that translates richness and elegance.

The lively and very frank attack precedes the acidulous roundness of the summer fruits expressed by the nose which are mingled with the refreshing flavors of exotic fruits (lychee, mango). Then, in delicate harmony, the fat and smells of fresh almond and pear are revealed. The finish, based on a stony minerality, is prolonged on notes of very ripe lemon.

name: Comte Lafond Sancerre Grande Cuvée
description: de Ladoucette from France, provided by Maisons Marques & Domaines. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Pouilly-Fumé
description: The delicate and complex olfactory expression opens on aromas which remind of white flower, exotic fruits. There is a very beautiful complexity for a vintage where the end-of-season’s sun brought a lot to the aromas. Excellent complexity that translates into great and elegant richness. Nice attack, straight and bright, it takes place with elegance on fruity notes associated with a dense structure and a beautiful acidity which brings a great length in the end of the mouth. There are aromas of exotic fruits (litchi, mango).

name: Sancerre Blanc La Poussie
description: A beautiful minerality brings a lovely character. The palate is round with a finesse offering the aromatic flavours of gingerbread, honey and peach. The finish is persistent and ends on a light and refreshing mineral note. The first notes are very fine, complex and delicate. The aromas of peaches, quince and white flowers follow. Light breathing reveals the delicate scents of exotic fruit. The minerality brings a beautiful equilibrium and harmony.

name: Black Pepper Vodka
description: Recently voted the Top Flavored Vodka in the world, Dixie Black Pepper Vodka is the must-have for any Bloody Mary or oyster shooter. After a week, we combine both batches to create a perfectly balanced pepper vodka.

name: Vodka Meyer Lemon
description:
Grays Peak Vodka is the summit of smoothness for vodka that is ideal straight or perfect for enhancing the flavors of any cocktail.

The purity of Grays Peak vodka is only achieved by using premium corn that is distilled five times using water that undergoes a proprietary reverse osmosis process that removes any trace minerals typically found in spring waters that can produce "hot" flavors.

Grays Peak Vodka is a gluten free vodka that is distilled from corn.

Available in;

Straight Vodka

Mountain Berry Flavored Vodka

Meyer Lemon Flavored Vodka

name: Shine Peppermint Stick Moonshine
description: Our peppermint stick moonshine meets the palate with a bright splash. The crisp taste is rounded out by a hint of light cocoa and cream. At 100 proof this shine packs a peppermint punch straight out of the jar. Use in mojitos, hot chocolate, or any cocktail that needs a blast of cool peppermint.

name: Sugarlands Shine Appalachian Apple Pie Moonshine
description:
Appalachian Apple Pie serves up a zesty taste of fresh baked green apples between two layers of shortbread, accented with a lemon zest. The fresh snap of green apple rounds out into a quick citrus finish with a lingering caramel cushion.

Our Apple Pie moonshine is a treat that speaks for itself. Unlike most apple pie moonshines, we don’t use red apple and pie spices; we start with a green apple flavor and layer in a sweet caramel taste to finish.

name: Sugarlands Shine Appalachian Apple Pie Moonshine
description:

name: Sugarlands Shine Artist Series Cole Swindell's Peppermint Moonshine
description: Cole Swindell’s Peppermint Moonshine meets the palate with a bright splash. The crisp taste is rounded out by a hint of light cocoa and cream. The velvety balance will leave you feeling refreshed, satisfied and warm inside

name: Sugarlands Shine Artist Series Cole Swindell's Pre-Show Punch Moonshine
description: Cole Swindell’s Pre Show Punch combines tropical flavors with hints of cherry. This easy sippin’, 50-proof ‘shine is really all you need. Just crack open the jar and enjoy the show.

name: Sugarlands Shine Blockader's Blackberry Moonshine
description: Blockader’s Blackberry Moonshine blends the natural flavors of ripe berries with the floral fragrances of honeysuckle and lavender. With a velvety mouthfeel and a long, nectarous finish.

name: Sugarlands Shine Blueberry Muffin Moonshine
description:
Our Blueberry Muffin moonshine layers fresh, bright blueberries with a crumbled streusel finish. This flavor is a great accent to many classic cocktails such as mojitos and lemon drops.

Sugarlands Blueberry Muffin moonshine is much different than other blueberry flavored spirits; in addition to a natural blueberry flavor there is a sweet strudel on the finish. This unique spirit makes tasty and beautiful cocktails with a rich blue color.

name: Sugarlands Shine Butterscotch Gold Moonshine
description: Butterscotch Gold brings out tastes of brown sugar, caramel, and vanilla that informs memories of kettle corn at the county fair. Slight hazelnut notes and a lingering cream flavor contribute to a long finish that cannot last long enough.

name: Sugarlands Shine Chipper Jone's Sweet Tea Moonshine
description: Sugarlands Distilling Company from United States, provided by Sugarlands Distilling. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Sugarlands Shine Legends Series Jim Tom's Signature Unaged Rye Moonshine
description: Jim Tom Hedrick’s Unaged Rye maintains an earthy balance between spicy rye and toasted grains with hints of black pepper. Distilled in Gatlinburg, this award-winning moonshine packs a potent enough punch to keep you sippin’.

name: Sugarlands Shine Legends Series Mark Rogers American Peach Moonshine
description: Mark Rogers’ American Peach boasts the natural taste of ripe summer peaches. When sipped, this sweet and velvety spirit will deliver a traditional warmth of moonshine.

name: Sugarlands Shine Legends Series Mark Rogers American Peach Moonshine
description: Mark Rogers’ American Peach boasts the natural taste of ripe summer peaches. When sipped, this sweet and velvety spirit will deliver a traditional warmth of moonshine.

name: Sugarlands Shine Legends Series Mark and Digger's Rye Apple Moonshine
description: Mark and Digger’s Rye Apple is an exquisite invention from the hills of East Tennessee. This unaged rye combines gala apples with traditional pie spices such as nutmeg, allspice, and clove. Rye Apple is quick to finish, but long to remember – the way any fine shine should be.

name: Sugarlands Shine Maple Bacon Moonshine
description: Maple Bacon moonshine is a sweet and savory spirit that combines the tastes of smoked bacon and candied maple syrup. The distinct blend is easily taken as a shot or combined to make a smoky, full-flavored cocktail.

name: Sugarlands Shine Peanut Butter & Jelly Moonshine
description: PB & J is a layered flavor; initially, you get a smoky peanut butter flavor followed by grape preserves. It’s a fun novelty flavor to share with friends at any party. Keep it in your freezer for optimal flavor straight from the jar!

name: Sugarlands Shine Piña Colada Moonshine
description:
Our Piña Colada moonshine combines the taste of fresh pineapple and coconut milk. This smooth, crisp, and sweet flavor is best enjoyed over ice or out of a blender.

This moonshine is coconut forward and finishes with a smooth pineapple flavor; with one sip you will feel like you’re sitting in a beach chair with your toes in the sand! But sip wisely, because at 70 proof it packs a hidden punch.

name: Sugarlands Shine Root Beer Moonshine
description: Our Root Beer Moonshine is simple, almost bubbly, and has the perfect touch of sweetness. The mellow mix of sassafras root, vanilla, and wintergreen make this offering a timeless classic.
